Description:
  The nifty_layout generator creates a basic layout, stylesheet and
  helper which will give some structure to a starting Rails app.

  The generator takes two optional arguments which will be the name of the
  layout and stylesheet files correspondingly. If no argument is passed
  then the default layout will be "application" and the default stylesheet
   will be nifty_layout. If only one argument is passed, it becomes both
   layout and stylesheet file name.

  The generator also takes options for template language for both layout
  and stylesheet files. Valid options are: --erb (default) or --haml,
  --css (default for erb), --sass (default for haml) or --scss.

  The helper module includes some methods which can be called in any
  template or partial to set variables to be used in the layout, such as
  page title and javascript/stylesheet includes.

Examples:
    rails generate nifty:layout

        Layout:     app/views/layouts/application.html.erb
        Stylesheet: app/assets/stylesheets/nifty_layout.css
        Helper:     app/helpers/layout_helper.rb


    rails generate nifty:layout admin

        Layout:     app/views/layouts/admin.html.erb
        Stylesheet: app/assets/stylesheets/admin.css
        Helper:     app/helpers/layout_helper.rb


    rails generate nifty:layout admin style

        Layout:     app/views/layouts/admin.html.erb
        Stylesheet: app/assets/stylesheets/style.css
        Helper:     app/helpers/layout_helper.rb


    rails generate nifty:layout --haml

        Layout:     app/views/layouts/application.html.haml
        Stylesheet: app/assets/stylesheets/nifty_layout.sass
        Helper:     app/helpers/layout_helper.rb


    rails generate nifty:layout --erb --scss

        Layout:     app/views/layouts/application.html.erb
        Stylesheet: app/assets/stylesheets/nifty_layout.css.scss
        Helper:     app/helpers/layout_helper.rb
